IMCMapper-Functions

Nicolas Damond

2018-09-24

MAIN FUNCTIONS

- CellMap: Displays 1 to 3 cell populations

- ChannelHM: Heatmap 1 to 3 channels

- CellsAndCounts: Heatmap 1 channel + highlight the borders of 1 to 3 cell populations

- ClusterDisplay: Display cell clusters (and unique continuous values)

- IMCDisplay: Display 1 to 3 raw IMC images

- CellsandIMC: Display 1 IMC image + highlight the borders of 1 to 3 cell populations

- IMCandCells: Display 1 to 3 IMC images + highlight the borders of 1 cell population

GENERAL REQUIREMENTS

R packages

  • “data.table”
  • “EBImage”

CellProfiler data

  • Cell masks (16-bit tiff files).
  • When exporting CSV from CellProfiler, in “Select measurements” > “Image”, you have to select FileName, PathName and Metadata.
  • This will generate an “Image.csv” file, which is required to run this script.

A data set in the data.table format

  • The cell objects must be the same as those used to create the masks in CellProfiler.
  • Must contain an “image” column where the values correspond to the image names in the “Metadata” column of your “Image.csv” file.
  • Must contain a “cell id” column in the format “###_nnn“, where ### is the name of the image in the”image" column and nnn is the number of the cell.

OPTIONAL ARGUMENTS

Those arguments can be passed to any of the functions below

Options for image display
method — ‘raster’ or ‘browser’ option from the EBImage package to display the images in a separate (new tab) JavaScript viewer (‘browser’) or directly in R (‘raster’) (default = ‘raster’).

Arguments for saving the images
save — TRUE/FALSE: should the images be saved (default = FALSE).

path — path to the folder in which the images should be saved. If the folder does not exist it will be created (default = working directory).

type — ‘png’, ‘jpeg’ or ‘tiff’: format of the saved images (default = ‘png’).

Arguments for legend customization
leg — TRUE/FALSE: should a color legend be displayed. The legend will be displayed as a separate image (default = TRUE). If “save” is set to TRUE, the legend will be saved together with the pictures as a .png image.

legend — vector containing the names of the elements displayed in the legend

fill — vector containing the colors to be displayed in the legend

border — vector containing the color of the legend borders

cex — size of the text of the legend (character expansion)

+ any other argument taken by the “legend” function (see ?legend)

Arguments for label customization
label — TRUE/FALSE: should the name of the image be displayed on the image (default = TRUE). Doesn’t work with the ‘browser’ method. The label is also not displayed on saved images.

label.txt — text to be display on the image label. The same text will be displayed on all images (default = name of the image)

label.color — color of the image label displayed on the image

label.cex — size of the text of the image name label (character expansion)

label.x — x position of the image name label

label.y — y position of the image name label

FUNCTIONS

CellMap

Display 1 to 3 cell populations

# Vectors containing the ids of cells to display
cell.pop.1 <- unique(cells[core %in% c("A01","B01","E08") & CellType=='beta']$id)
cell.pop.2 <- unique(cells[core %in% c("A01","B01","E08") & CellType=='alpha']$id)
cell.pop.3 <- unique(cells[core %in% c("A01","B01","E08") & CellType=='delta']$id)

CellMap(x = cells,
        id.col = 'id',
        cell1 = cell.pop.1,
        cell2 = cell.pop.2,
        cell3 = cell.pop.3,
        meta = '/home/nicolasd/Data/CM2017/cpoutput/All/All_ImagePathMapping.csv',
        path.col = 'ObjectsPathName_FilteredRescaledCellsExpand',
        file.col = 'ObjectsFileName_FilteredRescaledCellsExpand',
        slide.col = 'Metadata_Slide',
        borders = TRUE,
        legend = c('beta', 'alpha', 'delta'),
        label.color = "cyan",
        cex=1,
        label.cex=2,
        label.x=85
        # Optional arguments to save the images
        # save = TRUE,
        # path = '/home/nicolasd/Data/CM2017/CellMapper'
)

ChannelHM

Heatmap 1 to 3 channels

# List of images to display
image.list <- c("A01","B01","E08")

ChannelHM(x = cells,
          id.col = 'id',
          counts.col = 'c_counts_scaled',
          channel.col = 'channel',
          image.col = 'core',
          im.list = image.list,
          ch1 = 'PIN',
          ch2 = 'GCG',
          # ch3 = 'SST',
          bcg1 = c(0, 4, 2),
          bcg2 = c(0, 4, 2),
          bcg3 = c(0, 4, 2),
          meta = '/home/nicolasd/Data/CM2017/cpoutput/All/All_ImagePathMapping.csv',
          path.col = 'ObjectsPathName_FilteredRescaledCellsExpand',
          file.col = 'ObjectsFileName_FilteredRescaledCellsExpand',
          slide.col = 'Metadata_Slide',
          borders = FALSE,
          legend = c("Proinsulin", "Glucagon", "Somatostatin"),
          cex=1,
          label.cex=2,
          label.x=85
          # save = TRUE,
          # path = '/home/nicolasd/Data/CM2017/CellMapper'
)

CellsAndCounts

Heatmap one channel and highlight the borders of 1 to 3 cell populations.
Known bug: when intensity is high (white cells), the borders of cells that should be displayed become dimmer and can be hard/impossible to see.

# Vectors containing the ids of cells to display
cell.pop.1 <- unique(cells[core %in% c("A01","B01","E08") & CellType=='beta']$id)
cell.pop.2 <- unique(cells[core %in% c("A01","B01","E08") & CellType=='alpha']$id)
cell.pop.3 <- unique(cells[core %in% c("A01","B01","E08") & CellType=='delta']$id)

CellsAndCounts(x = cells,
               id.col = 'id',
               image.col = 'core',
               channel.col = 'channel',
               counts.col = 'c_counts_scaled',
               ch = 'PIN',
               cell1 = cell.pop.1,
               cell2 = cell.pop.2,
               cell3 = cell.pop.3,
               meta = '/home/nicolasd/Data/CM2017/cpoutput/All/All_ImagePathMapping.csv',
               path.col = 'ObjectsPathName_FilteredRescaledCellsExpand',
               file.col = 'ObjectsFileName_FilteredRescaledCellsExpand',
               slide.col = 'Metadata_Slide',
               bcg = c(0, 2, 1),
               legend = c("Proinsulin", "Beta cells", "Alpha cells", "Delta cells"),
               cex=1,
               label.cex=2,
               label.x=85
               # save = TRUE,
               # path = '/home/nicolasd/Data/CM2017/CellMapper'
)

ClusterDisplay

Display cell clusters or cell types

# List of images to display
image.list <- c("A01","B01","E08")

ClusterDisplay(x = cells,
               im.list = image.list,
               id.col = 'id',
               image.col = 'core',
               cluster.col = 'CellType',
               meta = '/home/nicolasd/Data/CM2017/cpoutput/All/All_ImagePathMapping.csv',
               path.col = 'ObjectsPathName_FilteredRescaledCellsExpand',
               file.col = 'ObjectsFileName_FilteredRescaledCellsExpand',
               slide.col = 'Metadata_Slide',
               borders = FALSE,
               bcg=c(0,1,1),
               label.color="yellow",
               cex=0.6,
               label.cex=2,
               label.x=85
               # save = TRUE,
               # path = '/home/nicolasd/Data/CM2017/CellMapper'
)

IMCDisplay

Display one to three channel(s) from an IMC image

# List of images to display
image.list <- c("A01","B01","E08")

IMCDisplay(x = cells,
           im.list = image.list,
           image.col = 'core',
           ch1 = 'Syn',
           ch2 = 'SMA',
           ch3 = 'CK19',
           bcg1 = c(0, 0.05, 1),
           bcg2 = c(0, 0.3, 1),
           bcg3 = c(0, 1, 1),
           meta = '/home/nicolasd/Data/CM2017/cpoutput/All/All_ImagePathMapping.csv',
           path.col = 'ObjectsPathName_FilteredRescaledCellsExpand',
           file.col = 'ObjectsFileName_FilteredRescaledCellsExpand',
           slide.col = 'Metadata_Slide',
           borders = FALSE,
           legend = c("Synaptophysin", "SMA", "Cytokeratin 19"),
           cex=1,
           label.cex=2,
           label.x=85
           # method = 'browser'
           # save = TRUE,
           # path = '/home/nicolasd/Data/CM2017/CellMapper'
)

CellsandIMC

Display 1 IMC image + highlight the borders of 1 to 3 cell populations

Additional requirements

The channel images should be in the same folder as the masks (one channel per image), similar to the histoCAT folder structure

# Vectors containing the ids of cells to display
cell.pop.1 <- unique(cells[core %in% c("A01","B01","E08") & CellType=='beta']$id)
cell.pop.2 <- unique(cells[core %in% c("A01","B01","E08") & CellType=='alpha']$id)
cell.pop.3 <- unique(cells[core %in% c("A01","B01","E08") & CellType=='delta']$id)

CellsandIMC(x = cells,
            id.col = 'id',
            image.col = 'core',
            ch = 'Pin',
            cell1 = cell.pop.1,
            cell2 = cell.pop.2,
            cell3 = cell.pop.3,
            meta = '/home/nicolasd/Data/CM2017/cpoutput/All/All_ImagePathMapping.csv',
            path.col = 'ObjectsPathName_FilteredRescaledCellsExpand',
            file.col = 'ObjectsFileName_FilteredRescaledCellsExpand',
            slide.col = 'Metadata_Slide',
            bcg = c(0, 0.05, 1),
            legend = c("Proinsulin", "Beta cells", "Alpha cells", "Delta cells"),
            cex=1,
            label.cex=2,
            label.x=85
            # save = TRUE,
            # path = '/home/nicolasd/Data/CM2017/CellMapper'
)

IMCandCells

Display 1 IMC image + highlight the borders of 1 to 3 cell populations

Additional requirements

The channel images should be in the same folder as the masks (one channel per image), similar to the histoCAT folder structure

# Vectors containing the ids of cells to display
cell.pop.1 <- unique(cells[core %in% c("A01","B01","E08") & CellType=='beta']$id)

IMCandCells(x = cells,
            id.col = 'id',
            image.col = 'core',
            cell1 = cell.pop.1,
            ch1 = 'Pin',
            ch2 = 'Gcg',
            ch3 = 'Sst',
            bcg1 = c(0, 0.05, 1),
            bcg2 = c(0, 0.1, 1),
            bcg3 = c(0, 0.2, 1),
            meta = '/home/nicolasd/Data/CM2017/cpoutput/All/All_ImagePathMapping.csv',
            path.col = 'ObjectsPathName_FilteredRescaledCellsExpand',
            file.col = 'ObjectsFileName_FilteredRescaledCellsExpand',
            slide.col = 'Metadata_Slide',
            legend = c("Beta cells", "Proinsulin", "Glucagon", "Somatostatin"),
            cex=1,
            label.cex=2,
            label.x=85
            # method = 'browser'
            # save = TRUE,
            # path = '/home/nicolasd/Data/CM2017/CellMapper'
)
